<HEADLINE>
A BOOK LOVER'S GUIDE FOR THOSE LAZY, HAZY DAYS OF SUMMER  
 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GRAB YOUR BEACH BLANKET AND A GOOD BOOK!...  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Editors: We are pleased once again to offer you a tempting
7-part list of recommended lawn-chair reading from the
highly-respected New York Times Book Review section.  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   For your ease, the extensive list has been moved to you in seven
easy-to-edit sections:
</P>
<P>
   Part 1 - Fiction: 1,400 words
</P>
<P>
   Part 2 - Fiction: 1,475 words
</P>
<P>
   Part 3 - Nonfiction: 900 words
</P>
<P>
   Part 4 - Nonfiction: 900 words
</P>
<P>
   Part 5 - Nonfiction: 850 words
</P>
<P>
   Part 6 - Nonfiction: 900 words
</P>
<P>
   Part 7 - Mysteries &AMP; Science Fiction: 575 words.  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ...THIS PACKAGE IS SLUGGED
BC-VACATION-READING-PART()of7-NYTSF...  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   To publish any or all of this seven-part list of summertime
reading from The New York Times Book Review section, it must be
purchased _ the rate is not prohibitive _ from New York Times
Syndicate sales representative DEBRA WEYDERT at 732-390-4480 or fax
her at 732-390-4697. If unable to reach Ms. Weydert, please call us
at 800-444-0267.  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Give her a call _ and your readers something to read!
</P>
</TEXT>
