school, which I will not because I'd rather be on my feet for eight
hours straight scanning groceries than alone in a room with 25
children, I've decided I would teach kindergarten. And not because
5-year-olds are cute and sweet. They're not. No, I'd teach
kindergarten because I've decided kindergarten teachers get all the
good gifts. (Minor, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
