100s, lows in the morning (for about five minutes) from 72 to 77.
So you're new to town, and you've never dealt with Texas heat. How
do you stand it? Here are a few helpful tips on how to survive
summer. (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
