left behind in Florida a semi-comatose father in hospice care. His
dream of college ended with his father's sudden death. The prism of
Daddy's frustrated hopes was the lens through which I viewed the
entire weekend. For me, then and now, he provokes the question: How
do we honor the past that paved a better future? (Jefferson, Palm
Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
