<P>
   FOOD-HONEY _ Like most of what we eat, there is a season _ even
for honey. In early May, the only honey in tended hives was at the
bottom, reserved for the bees. But then flats to collect the fresh
nectar were installed in the top of each hive and the bees went to
work. In a few weeks, Ray Alley, a beekeeper who sells his honey at
the Warren County (Ohio) Farm Market, will be able to start
bottling this year's production of an estimated 700 quarts. (Dayton
Daily News).
