   VIDEO-COLUMN _ This summer marks 100th anniversary of Alfred
Hitchcock's birth. New York's MOMA has a retrospective already
under way and the High Museum here starts one Friday with
``Vertigo'' (others in the High series: ``The 39 Steps,'' ``The
Wrong Man,'' ``Suspicion,'' ``Strangers on a Train,'' ``Dial M For
Murder'' and ``Psycho''). You can delve into Hitchcock's masterful
work yourself on video. Here's what to look for while watching some
of his films on video, including ``The Lady Vanishes,'' ``North by
Northwest,'' ``The Birds,'' ``Foreign Correspondent,'' ``Shadow of
a Doubt'' and Hitchcock's only best picture winner ``Rebecca.''
(BLongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 24.
