<P>
   MINOR-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ If I were to ever teach
school, which I will not because I'd rather be on my feet for eight
hours straight scanning groceries than alone in a room with 25
children, I've decided I would teach kindergarten. And not because
5-year-olds are cute and sweet. They're not. No, I'd teach
kindergarten because I've decided kindergarten teachers get all the
good gifts. (Minor, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ What with the success of his first published
novel, I thought Bob Mrazek would be as happy as a pig in mud. But
dealing with Hollywood for the film rights, he is beginning to feel
a bit soiled. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
<P>
   CERABINO-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ They're having trouble
finding nominees for the Great Floridians Program. Really. It's
getting so bad, they might have to settle for a Pretty Good
Floridians Program. I'll explain. (Cerabino, Palm Beach Post)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ The heat is on us like a
cockroach on a cat food dish. Friends and neighbors, here's your
weather forecast for the next 3 2/3 months: Highs in the 90s to
100s, lows in the morning (for about five minutes) from 72 to 77.
So you're new to town, and you've never dealt with Texas heat. How
do you stand it? Here are a few helpful tips on how to survive
summer. (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   JEFFERSON-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ ``This time a week
ago, we were at ``The Last Lecture'' . . . the Dean's Brunch . . .
`` I play this mind game daily, trying to keep vivid the details of
our trip last month to attend our youngest son's graduation from
Northwestern Law School. When my husband and I flew to Chicago, I
left behind in Florida a semi-comatose father in hospice care. His
dream of college ended with his father's sudden death. The prism of
Daddy's frustrated hopes was the lens through which I viewed the
entire weekend. For me, then and now, he provokes the question: How
do we honor the past that paved a better future? (Jefferson, Palm
Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
