1999 national cookbook awards. (Rice, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   RATINGS _ WASHINGTON _ The voluntary rating systems that parents
and the government are relying on to protect children from
excessive sex and violence in media are unreliable tools, watchdog
groups say. These systems _ largely run by the film, television,
video game and music industries themselves _ often ignore or
downplay objectionable material, or engage in ``ratings creep'' in
which a category allows more extreme content over time, they say.
(Dart, Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (e) entertainment and (w) Washington categories.
