<P>
   MAINE-AIR-RAGE (Bangor, Maine) _ During the past 31 days, three
airliners have made emergency landings in Bangor to remove British
passengers who have gone into violent rages during transatlantic
flights. While other airports might shrink from airborne discipline
problems, Bangor is marketing its willingness to handle them. By
Ellen Barry. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   N.H.-GUNS (Nashua) _ As Congress struggles to approve
gun-control measures this week, so the state of New Hampshire
struggles, too. By Jill Zuckman. 800 words.
