   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NYHAN-COLUMN (Undated) -- George W. Bush's early success has
cast a pall over all other candidacies, but none has been eclipsed
more than that of Lamar Alexander. By David Nyhan. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   NOLAN-COLUMN (San Francisco) -- Planners for a new Fenway Park
would do well to heed the famous landscape architect Frederick Law
Olmsted, who touted ``turf, trees, water, and other natural
objects.'' By Martin F. Nolan. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   JACKSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ There is an honest desperation about
the lawsuits being filed against gun makers 20 cities. There was no
alternative as Congress plays the hit man for the National Rifle
Association. By Derrick Jackson. 922 words.
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-COLUMN (Undated) -- How one priest is defending the New
Testament. By Diego Ribadeneira.
