   POW-REUNION _ (Burbank) _ While an elementary student, history
teacher David Thomson wore a POW bracelet inscribed with Harold
Johnson's name until he was released. Upon his return, Johnson sent
Thomson a thank you letter, but the two have not had contact since.
Thomson talked about it to his Burbank High School students during
a history lesson on Vietnam. The students tracked Johnson down on
the Internet -- he's now a mayor in Iowa -- and chipped in to bring
him to the school to surprise their teacher. By Mary Lou Aurelio.
(Will move on the ``a'' nation and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   WHITTAKER-MERGER (Simi Valley) _ Simi Valley-based Whittaker
Corp. announced Wednesday it will be bought by Meggitt PLC. The
merger agreement _ with a price tag of $380 million, or $28 per
share _ has been approved by the boards of directors of Whittaker
and Meggitt. By Ben Sullivan. (Will move on the ``f'' financial
news wire.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
