prevent.
</P>
<P>
   And, we are entitled to ask, was it a ``war'' at all? In a war,
do not two sides engage each other in battle, and both sides suffer
casualties?
</P>
<P>
   But Kosovo 1999 will feature on no regimental roll of honor.
This was among the very few wars fought not in pursuit of national
interests but for reasons of simple humanity. However, there is no
sense of triumph, or of virtue rewarded.
</P>
<P>
   There might have been, had NATO suffered some casualties or had
Milosevic _ architect of a decade of misery in the Balkans _ been
overthrown. But he has not been, despite a one-sided contest in
which the Allies have not lost a single life in battle.
</P>
<P>
   This has been war by remote control, carried out by deadly
