<HEADLINE>
COVER: MUSIC SPOTLIGHTS COUNTRY SINGER FAITH HILL 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By MALCOLM MAYHEW 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FAITH HILL
</P>
<P>
   Home base: Born in Star, Miss.; now lives in Nashville.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 31.
</P>
<P>
   Claim to fame: Babe country singer with red-hot single ``This
Kiss,'' and an upcoming concert.
</P>
<P>
   Interesting factoid: Faith Hill is married to country singer Tim
McGraw. They have two daughters, Gracie Katherine, 2, and Maggie
Elizabeth, 8 months.
</P>
<P>
   The story so far: Faith Hill could be described as the queen of
Nashville right now. Since 1993, when she released her debut disc,
``Take Me As I Am,'' she has won countless industry awards, sold
millions of records and, most recently, appeared in VH1's Divas
Live concert, which also featured pop heavyweights Tina Turner and
Whitney Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Great ``Kiss'': Her recent spate of success, Hill will be the
first to admit, is mostly thanks to her single, ``This Kiss,''
which has crossed over to pop-music territory.
</P>
<P>
   ``This song has changed my career,'' Hill said in a recent news
service interview. ``VH1 never would have invited me to Divas Live
before this.''
</P>
<P>
   Hill says that even though she's scheduled to be all over
country and pop radio, conquering pop music is not her goal.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not seeking a pop career,'' she says. ``But if it happens,
great. I'm just going to make music that comes from my heart. If it
works someplace else, I'll welcome it.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
