<HEADLINE>
VIDEO-GAME REVIEWS 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By NATHAN SCHNURMAN, MALCOLM MAYHEW 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LODE RUNNER 3-D (Infogrames/Big Bang Software for Nintendo 64,
all ages)
</P>
<P>
   Description: Lode Runner 3-D is a fun and educational mind
puzzle. It challenges body, mind and soul while entertaining you
with terrific 3-D graphics.
</P>
<P>
   High points: A high point with Lode Runner 3-D is that it has
five different worlds, with five different stages and four levels
in each stage. Another high point is that beginners can practice an
easy level before going on to a more challenging and complicated
level.
</P>
<P>
   Low points: A low point about Lode Runner is that after a
certain amount of time it tends to get boring. Also, the music
starts to get on your nerves and you have to turn the volume down.
Another low point is that if you die or restart a level (which you
commonly do) it takes quite a while to load.
</P>
<P>
   At times, it was very mind-bogglin'. But its low points keep you
from coming back for more.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's A - F rating: C.
</P>
<P>
   KEN GRIFFEY JR.'S SLUGFEST (Nintendo for Nintendo 64, all ages)
</P>
<P>
   Description: Nintendo's popular baseball series graduates to the
Nintendo 64 _ with great results.
</P>
<P>
   High points: The graphics are excellent _ wonderfully detailed
and pinpoint accurate. Use an Expansion Pak, sold separately, and
they're better. Also, most of the players, teams and stadiums are
here, and the controls are easy to understand and maneuver.
</P>
<P>
   Low points: Slugfest doesn't have all the options as some of the
PlayStation baseball games do, and Nintendo's attempts at creating
realism often fail. Example: While playing a game at the Ballpark
at Arlington, players hear a train roar by. Is there a railroad
near the Ballpark we don't know about?
</P>
<P>
   But Slugfest has great graphics and fluid gameplay. It's easily
one of the better baseball games out there right now.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's A - F rating: A minus.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
