<HEADLINE>
CD REVIEW: BACKSTREET BOYS' MILLENNIUM 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By ANGELICA LARA 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Is Backstreet really back? They certainly are with their new CD
``Millennium,'' which features their current hit single, ``I Want
It That Way.''
</P>
<P>
   The CD shows how much these boys have matured over the last
year.
</P>
<P>
   The songs are no longer just sunny pop but hip-hop dance music
and heart-melting love ballads. If you're into songs that make you
want to go hug someone, then you'll like ``The Perfect Fan,'' a
tribute to their mothers.
</P>
<P>
   If you aren't the sentimental type, you might like the
move-your-body track, ``Larger Than Life.'' This song is both sweet
and great to dance to; it thanks the fans but also tells about the
down side of success, all the while keeping you moving.
</P>
<P>
   So unless you really hate the Backstreet Boys, I recommend you
get down to the nearest store and pick up ``Millennium,'' even if
it is just for the cover pictures.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
