s e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TV-MINI-SERIES-$ADV13     06-09 0544
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TV-MINI-SERIES-$ADV13-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TOP 7 REASONS TO KICK THE MINI-SERIES HABIT NOW  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, JUNE 13) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 By RON WERTHEIMER   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   What a spring this has been for the mini-series! From Noah's ark
to Joan of Arc, the subjects have spanned the spectrum. But what's
coming for the fall? While the next round of
plucked-from-the-headlines topics have yet to be plucked from the
headlines, other projects are quickly moving forward.
</P>
<P>
   Although these have not been announced, sources close to
observers (who spoke on the condition of anonymity) have revealed
some of the top-secret plans. You heard it here first. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CORIOLANUS Cashing in on the Shakespeare craze, the producers
have cannily cast the king of the mini-series, Peter Strauss, in
the title role of the haughty patrician warrior, with Jane Seymour
as his wife, Virgilia, and Della Reese as his mother, Volumnia. Don
Johnson and Cheech Marin play the evil Tribunes Brutus and
Sicinius.
</P>
<P>
   THE CANTERBURY TALES If they like Shakespeare, they'll love
Chaucer. Besides, those tales will fit perfectly around the
commercials. The innovative casting includes Michael J. Fox as the
Clerk, George Wendt as the Cook, Tim Allen as the Friar, David
Schwimmer as the Knight, Peter Strauss as the Squire and Calista
Flockhart as the Wife of Bath.
</P>
<P>
   GROVER CLEVELAND John Goodman has nearly agreed to star as the
only man big enough to have been both the 22nd and 24th presidents.
Drew Carey plays his pal Teddy Roosevelt. The highlight of the
second installment, of course, is Cleveland's White House wedding
to his former ward Frances Folsom (Jane Seymour). Cameos include
Peter Strauss as James G. Blaine.
</P>
<P>
   STATE FAIR The recent success of the latest version of Rodgers
and Hammerstein's ``Cinderella'' has sent the producers dipping
back into the work of those plucky tunesmiths. Making his network
singing debut, Peter Strauss plays the happy farmer who takes his
prize pig Blue Boy (Babe) to the fair. Calista Flockhart plays the
farmer's dreamy daughter, who falls for the sharpy reporter (Tim
Allen). Jason Alexander is the farmer's dreamy son who falls for
the sharpy band singer (Shelley Long). Jane Seymour plays Mom.
</P>
<P>
   THE FRENCH REVOLUTION The Czech Republic has inked a deal to
play France during the era of its greatest tribulation, with the
entire population of Switzerland agreeing to take two months off
from whatever it is they do to portray the French. Peter Strauss
will be Louis, Kirstie Alley will be Marie Antoinette, and Kelsey
Grammer will be Robespierre.
</P>
<P>
   THE PHIL RIZZUTO STORY Peter Strauss stars as the plucky kid
from Brooklyn who becomes a beloved Yankee shortstop. Ted Danson
has signed to play Yogi Berra, with Tim Allen as Mickey Mantle,
Kelsey Grammer as Whitey Ford and John Ritter as Casey Stengel.
</P>
<P>
   LEWIS AND CLARK Ted Danson and Mary Steenburgen star as those
fearless explorers, with Jimmy Smits as Thomas Jefferson and
Calista Flockhart as Sacajawea, their intrepid Indian guide. To add
family interest, the animals of the forests and plains will be
played by beloved actors, including John Goodman as the buffalo,
Scott Wolf as the fox, Michael J. Fox as the wolf and Peter Strauss
as the beaver.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
